post_text:
Attention GPS families:
As of August 31, 2020, the USDA has extended the Summer Food Service Program
This allows schools to offer meals to all children at no charge this fall to minimize the challenges of meals during the pandemic
If your child has eaten school meals during the month of September, your meals will be reimbursed into your family lunch account.
Your child will still need to bring his meal card to lunch and breakfast to be scanned as it is the best way to get an accurate meal count. When the card is scanned, no accounts will be charged for the initial meal. Your account will be charged as usual if your child purchases 2nd entrees or milks.
This will run through December 22, 2020 or as funds are available.

Attention GPS families:
As of August 31, 2020, the USDA has extended the Summer Food Service Program

If your child has eaten school meals during the month of September, your meals will be reimbursed into your family lunch account.

This will run through December 22, 2020 or as funds are available.

We look forward to the start of a great school year and I know you are excited as well. Have a great evening

post_text:
Good evening, this is Seth Ryker, Secondary Principal for Gothenburg Public Schools calling with an important update regarding the Commencement Ceremony scheduled for Saturday, August 1st.
At the recommendation of both our local health care officials and our regional department of public health the decision has been made to cancel the Graduation Ceremony. This recommendation is directly tied to the current rate of infection within the community of Gothenburg. Graduates are asked to stop by the school to pick up diplomas on either Tuesday, July 28th or Monday, August 3rd between the hours of 8:00 and 4:00. Students wishing to take a picture can bring their cap and gown and have their picture taken. The picture along with a statement of congratulations will be shared on social media.

To the Class of 2020 we wish you good luck and we know that you will make us all proud.

post_text:
The driving portion of driver education will resume June 8th. However, there are some precautions (COVID 19) that must be taken before a student is allowed to drive.

1. A waiver MUST be signed by a parent/guardian. The waiver form is in the high school office. Waiver form must be signed and left at the office before you are notified to set up drive times.

2. A mask must be worn by the driver and instructor.

3. Student's temperature will be taken prior to driving.

4. One student per session and touch points in the vehicle will be disinfected following each use.

5. Student's driving permit must be on person.

Questions may be directed to steve.reeves@goswedes.org

GHS 8-11 Students: your opportunity to request classes for next year is set for this Thursday & Friday:

Class Of 2021 @ NOON on Thursday
Class Of 2022 @ 12:45 pm on Thursday
Class Of 2023 @ NOON on Friday
Class Of 2024 @ 12:45 pm on Friday

Prior to this Zoom meeting:
* Know what elective classes you'd like to take (you can view course descriptions on our school's website under "Departments"). Elective classes are filled on a "1st come, 1st serve" basis.
* Visit with your English, Math, and Science teachers to determine your next level of core class in these areas.
* Be sure you are meeting all graduation requirements.
* Be able to access your PowerSchool.
* Have your Chromebook charged!!

Take advantage of this opportunity to pre-register for classes. Placing your requests now will insure a spot for you in certain elective / core classes.
Should you not pre-register, Mr. Wiggins will create a schedule for you.............

While we continue online learning at Gothenburg Public Schools, we are making every effort to ensure student safety comes first. We are using platforms and security measures that allow us to safely communicate via video with our students. The attached image from National Online Safety is for reference purposes only as it contains some great tips for students, parents, and teachers. With the social distancing measures we now have in place in Nebraska, some of the platforms mentioned might also be used for personal communication with grandparents and other family members with whom you’d like to remain connected.
As always, we welcome you to contact your child’s teacher or our tech team (chromebookhelp@gothenburgswedes.org)
if you have any questions about the technology being used to deliver our online classes.
Thank you for all you do to ensure your student stays connected with us!

post_text: It's time for another #wakeupWednesday from Dudley Library! Today's focus is the widely popular app "Snapchat". While age restrictions are clearly marked 13+, it's oftentimes used by kids much younger. This guide from National Online Safety is meant to showcase information about Snapchat that will help parents and students identify potential issues with the app as well as safeguards that can be put in place to make the app as safe as possible for its users. As always, please contact amy.harrison@goswedes.org with any questions.

It's time for another #wakeupWednesday from Dudley Library! Each week on Wednesday, we will feature an infographic containing information about safety as it relates to online/internet safety for students and even adults!
This week's infographic from National Online Safety focuses on a popular social-media app called TikTok. Widely popular, this app is best used by those that understand its full capabilities and some of its options that should be used with discretion.
As always, please contact amy.harrison@goswedes.org with any questions.

A reminder that GPS has a change to the school calendar next week. Parent-teacher conferences will be held on Tuesday, February 4th in the evening from 5:00-8:00 and on Friday, February 7th in the morning from 7AM-9AM.

Because of parent-teacher conferences, there will be a 2:30pm dismissal on Tuesday, February 4th and NO SCHOOL on Friday, February 7th.

We will have a regular, 3:30 dismissal time on Monday, Wednesday, and Thursday next week.
